101
00:07:10,115 --> 00:07:18,221
♪ ♪

102
00:07:28,583 --> 00:07:31,585
[militaristic drum and
bugle music playing]

103
00:07:31,586 --> 00:07:39,692
♪ ♪

104
00:07:44,098 --> 00:07:47,199
[wind whistling]

105
00:07:54,115 --> 00:07:56,281
Got to get your rest, Sam.

106
00:07:56,283 --> 00:07:57,800
You're so peaked;

107
00:07:57,818 --> 00:08:00,219
you look like death eating a cracker.

108
00:08:01,739 --> 00:08:02,954
General.

109
00:08:02,957 --> 00:08:04,741
Any word from the rangers?

110
00:08:04,742 --> 00:08:07,744
No, sir.

111
00:08:07,745 --> 00:08:10,747
I have an army of
untrained, undisciplined,

112
00:08:10,748 --> 00:08:12,464
ill-equipped men and not enough of 'em.

113
00:08:12,466 --> 00:08:15,467
That's why I can't sleep.

114
00:08:15,469 --> 00:08:17,921
You got this wound
20-some odd years ago,

115
00:08:17,922 --> 00:08:19,137
and it still festers?

116
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,823
Damn it.

117
00:08:20,841 --> 00:08:22,825
Huh? Yes.

118
00:08:22,843 --> 00:08:24,993
1814... Battle of Horseshoe Bend.

119
00:08:25,012 --> 00:08:26,612
Musket ball.

120
00:08:28,015 --> 00:08:31,184
Caught a red stick arrow
in the groin there too.

121
00:08:31,185 --> 00:08:35,739
Thanks to the Great Spirit,
my manhood remained intact.

122
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:38,490
[chuckles]

123
00:08:38,492 --> 00:08:40,659
Little chips of splintered bone

124
00:08:40,661 --> 00:08:43,262
still working their way out.

125
00:08:44,832 --> 00:08:46,831
I sent Bowie to Travis with an order

126
00:08:46,834 --> 00:08:50,453
to blow up the Alamo, abandon it.

127
00:08:50,454 --> 00:08:52,678
I can't imagine what a trial it must be

128
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:54,841
to live with this.

129
00:08:54,842 --> 00:08:57,192
Sir, Baker and Sherman

130
00:08:57,211 --> 00:08:59,095
are still waiting to see you.

131
00:08:59,096 --> 00:09:00,713
Much obliged.

132
00:09:00,714 --> 00:09:03,633
"Here to be seen seeing
me" is more like it.

133
00:09:03,634 --> 00:09:06,803
Delegation's arrived to say,
"Attack the Mexicans."

134
00:09:06,804 --> 00:09:09,606
(Houston) Huh, delegation!

135
00:09:09,607 --> 00:09:13,560
Well, by God, come in this
instant, if not sooner.

136
00:09:13,561 --> 00:09:17,564
There's Juan Seguín too, sir.

137
00:09:17,565 --> 00:09:20,733
With due regard to the urgency
of your call, gentlemen,

138
00:09:20,734 --> 00:09:23,719
I hope you don't mind me
answering a call of my own.

139
00:09:23,737 --> 00:09:28,958
General, we mean no ill regard.

140
00:09:28,959 --> 00:09:34,062
We're just curious to what your plan is.

141
00:09:34,081 --> 00:09:36,064
I sent Deaf Smith and
his rangering company

142
00:09:36,083 --> 00:09:39,234
to report on the Alamo situation.

143
00:09:39,253 --> 00:09:41,754
Until I hear back,

144
00:09:41,755 --> 00:09:44,557
it'd be damn stupid to fix on any plan.

145
00:09:44,558 --> 00:09:46,241
There's only one plan.

146
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:48,094
Attack the Alamo.

147
00:09:48,095 --> 00:09:51,815
Mosley, I think you know me
better than to address me

148
00:09:51,816 --> 00:09:53,516
like I'm some dumb son of a bitch.

149
00:09:53,517 --> 00:09:55,101
(Sherman) I cannot
imagine your intention

150
00:09:55,102 --> 00:09:58,771
is to abandon those men, sir.

151
00:09:58,772 --> 00:10:00,523
It's what Davy Crockett's promising

152
00:10:00,524 --> 00:10:01,741
to keep their spirits hopeful.

153
00:10:01,742 --> 00:10:04,909
Juan, how many men are we?

154
00:10:04,912 --> 00:10:06,112
(Seguín) 374...

155
00:10:06,113 --> 00:10:08,764
by this morning's count.

156
00:10:08,782 --> 00:10:11,266
What are our supplies?

157
00:10:11,285 --> 00:10:14,120
Two days of beans, no meat,

158
00:10:14,121 --> 00:10:17,773
and we're certainly short of
muskets, powder, and shot.

159
00:10:20,511 --> 00:10:23,213
Let me understand this.

160
00:10:23,214 --> 00:10:26,097
You think we ought to
attack 5,000 well-armed,

161
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:30,118
well-fed Mexican veterans
supported by artillery.

162
00:10:30,137 --> 00:10:31,971
We do have the element of surprise, sir.

163
00:10:31,972 --> 00:10:33,273
(Houston) Huh!

164
00:10:33,274 --> 00:10:36,142
It does not matter how many there are.

165
00:10:36,143 --> 00:10:38,895
They are only Mexicans.

166
00:10:38,896 --> 00:10:41,231
Juan!

167
00:10:41,232 --> 00:10:43,816
You're a fool, Mosley.

168
00:10:43,817 --> 00:10:46,969
I should let Seguín here
cut your tongue out.

169
00:10:46,987 --> 00:10:50,973
General, what of Colonel
Fannin's relief column?

170
00:10:50,991 --> 00:10:54,878
George, tell them the
status on Colonel Fannin.

171
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:56,045
Our courageous colonel

172
00:10:56,046 --> 00:10:58,248
was on his way to the Alamo

173
00:10:58,249 --> 00:11:01,668
when two wagons broke
down betwixt and between.

174
00:11:01,669 --> 00:11:06,055
So he decided to change
course and return to Goliad.

175
00:11:06,056 --> 00:11:07,656
That is all the more reason

176
00:11:07,675 --> 00:11:10,492
we need to reinforce
Travis and Jim Bowie.

177
00:11:10,511 --> 00:11:13,495
Sam, what would your

178
00:11:13,514 --> 00:11:17,616
personal compunctions lead you to do?

179
00:11:20,237 --> 00:11:23,606
I will tell you what I'm not gonna do.

180
00:11:23,607 --> 00:11:27,076
I'm not gonna sacrifice
what little army I have

181
00:11:27,077 --> 00:11:29,779
by charging pell-mell
into Mexican lances.

182
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:33,116
I will not fight Santa Anna
the way he wants us to fight,

183
00:11:33,117 --> 00:11:35,952
nor the way you think I should.

184
00:11:35,953 --> 00:11:37,686
Gentlemen,

185
00:11:37,705 --> 00:11:40,385
Texas is struggling to break free

186
00:11:40,386 --> 00:11:41,857
from an oppressive regime.

187
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:43,092
No.

188
00:11:43,093 --> 00:11:44,761
We must fight for our independence

189
00:11:44,762 --> 00:11:46,678
like George Washington
and our forefathers

190
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:49,848
fought for theirs... with
speed and mobility.

191
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:51,134
Fall back.

192
00:11:51,135 --> 00:11:54,036
Live to fight another day.

193
00:11:54,054 --> 00:11:58,558
Deaf Smith and his rangers
have the right idea.

194
00:11:58,559 --> 00:12:00,024
As your commander,

195
00:12:00,027 --> 00:12:03,045
I will decide when the
day is right to do more.

196
00:12:05,115 --> 00:12:07,650
Now that you've been elucidated,

197
00:12:07,651 --> 00:12:11,821
get the hell out!

198
00:12:11,822 --> 00:12:13,221
General.

199
00:12:15,659 --> 00:12:18,760
- Juan.
- General.

200
00:12:21,832 --> 00:12:24,667
If it means anything,

201
00:12:24,668 --> 00:12:28,838
your amigos at the Alamo
call out to me in my dreams.

202
00:12:28,839 --> 00:12:32,008
[solemn music]

203
00:12:32,009 --> 00:12:39,182
♪ ♪

204
00:12:39,183 --> 00:12:41,283
[clunking]

205
00:12:42,603 --> 00:12:43,919
[laughter and water splashing]

206
00:12:43,937 --> 00:12:44,937
Whoo!

207
00:12:44,938 --> 00:12:46,939
- Whoo-hoo!
- Whoo!

208
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:48,740
(Fincham) You still get
a buck and two bits

209
00:12:48,742 --> 00:12:50,526
a day working for the army?

210
00:12:50,527 --> 00:12:52,829
(Burns) Rangers don't work
for the army, Truett.

211
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:54,546
We're working with the army.

212
00:12:54,548 --> 00:12:56,833
That's right. They don't give us orders.

213
00:12:56,834 --> 00:13:00,936
They offer us recommendations
and suggestions.

214
00:13:00,954 --> 00:13:03,285
Son, I give you a suggestion, by God,

215
00:13:03,286 --> 00:13:05,085
you best know it's a damn order.

216
00:13:05,086 --> 00:13:06,086
Sir.

217
00:13:06,087 --> 00:13:07,955
[laughs]

218
00:13:07,956 --> 00:13:10,291
Hey, don't expect to get
paid anytime soon, boys.

219
00:13:10,292 --> 00:13:12,042
Texas ain't got no money.

220
00:13:12,043 --> 00:13:14,345
Least not till we run
the bean-eaters out.

221
00:13:14,346 --> 00:13:15,695
No offense, Flores.

222
00:13:15,697 --> 00:13:17,515
You's a good bean-eater.

223
00:13:17,516 --> 00:13:18,531
I like you.

224
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:22,768
[shouting in Spanish]

225
00:13:22,771 --> 00:13:23,769
[water splashing]

226
00:13:23,772 --> 00:13:25,121
What the hell did you say?

227
00:13:25,140 --> 00:13:29,443
[cheering and laughter]

228
00:13:29,444 --> 00:13:31,244
Ask him.

229
00:13:37,319 --> 00:13:39,252
Deaf?

230
00:13:41,156 --> 00:13:42,373
Deaf?

231
00:13:42,374 --> 00:13:43,657
[rock clatters]

232
00:13:43,658 --> 00:13:45,993
What?

233
00:13:45,994 --> 00:13:47,661
Well, after General Houston

234
00:13:47,662 --> 00:13:50,047
quit being governor of Tennessee,

235
00:13:50,048 --> 00:13:52,550
is it true that he lit
out for the territory,

236
00:13:52,551 --> 00:13:54,218
took up with a Cherokee squaw,

237
00:13:54,219 --> 00:13:56,003
and stayed drunk for five years?

238
00:13:56,004 --> 00:14:00,224
I don't know he was drunk every day.

239
00:14:00,225 --> 00:14:03,493
(man) Ask about his Tennessee bride.

240
00:14:03,511 --> 00:14:07,348
What about his tender young wife?

241
00:14:07,349 --> 00:14:08,682
Why'd he leave her

242
00:14:08,683 --> 00:14:10,568
and quit being governor?

243
00:14:10,569 --> 00:14:13,103
Those your words, Henry?

244
00:14:13,104 --> 00:14:14,271
"Tender young wife"?

245
00:14:14,272 --> 00:14:15,940
Ooh! [laughs]

246
00:14:15,941 --> 00:14:17,191
(man) That's a whole heap nicer

247
00:14:17,192 --> 00:14:20,176
than I would've called her.

248
00:14:20,195 --> 00:14:22,679
I guess she rejected him.

249
00:14:22,697 --> 00:14:25,366
He felt compelled to leave her...

250
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:27,201
by honor, Henry.

251
00:14:27,202 --> 00:14:28,502
Mm-hmm.

252
00:14:28,503 --> 00:14:31,187
What I heard is, he
attacked her unnaturally.

253
00:14:31,206 --> 00:14:33,207
Now, I heard she had
the organs of a man

254
00:14:33,208 --> 00:14:35,125
under the... oh, yeah, yeah.

255
00:14:35,126 --> 00:14:36,509
That's a good one.

256
00:14:36,511 --> 00:14:39,028
Y'all know I can't hear nothing,

257
00:14:39,047 --> 00:14:40,547
and I certainly can't read your lips.

258
00:14:40,548 --> 00:14:42,482
You're sitting all back there.

259
00:14:46,021 --> 00:14:48,472
Now, nobody knows what happened
between the two of them,

260
00:14:48,473 --> 00:14:50,689
but I do know that Sam Houston's

261
00:14:50,692 --> 00:14:52,542
never spoken a word against her,

262
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:56,713
nor has he allowed one
spoken in his presence.

263
00:14:56,731 --> 00:15:00,717
What does that tell you?

264
00:15:00,735 --> 00:15:03,219
Reckon the same thing it tells you...

265
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:09,375
That you have a grasp of things

266
00:15:09,377 --> 00:15:13,012
the way we can't sometimes, Erastus.

267
00:15:13,014 --> 00:15:14,781
Let's move out.

268
00:15:18,003 --> 00:15:19,385
- Rest time's over, boys.
- [coughs]

269
00:15:19,387 --> 00:15:20,386
(Karnes) Saddle up.

270
00:15:20,388 --> 00:15:22,488
[coughing]

271
00:15:26,011 --> 00:15:27,393
(Karnes) General Sam Houston

272
00:15:27,395 --> 00:15:29,562
is a better man than his detractors.

273
00:15:29,564 --> 00:15:31,732
(Elwood) Then why in the hell
ain't he leading his army

