you know, too unnecessarily cruel.

558
00:29:55,075 --> 00:29:57,910
But we know now we were wrong.

559
00:29:57,911 --> 00:30:01,747
Arredondo was not harsh enough,

560
00:30:01,748 --> 00:30:03,916
and this is why we're fighting today...

561
00:30:03,917 --> 00:30:08,603
because he was not harsh enough.

562
00:30:11,975 --> 00:30:15,261
I will win this battle.

563
00:30:15,262 --> 00:30:16,762
I will win it for you.

564
00:30:16,763 --> 00:30:18,514
So 20 years from now,

565
00:30:18,515 --> 00:30:20,516
you will not have to
lead your sons north

566
00:30:20,517 --> 00:30:22,250
to fight this war again,

567
00:30:22,269 --> 00:30:26,772
because Santa Anna, like
Arredondo before him,

568
00:30:26,773 --> 00:30:30,508
was not man enough to win
it once and for all.

569
00:30:33,330 --> 00:30:35,448
I don't fight for Texas.

570
00:30:35,449 --> 00:30:38,117
I don't care about politics.

571
00:30:38,118 --> 00:30:39,785
Then why do you fight?

572
00:30:39,786 --> 00:30:43,054
It's in my blood, like this bird.

573
00:30:44,508 --> 00:30:46,375
Does the blood make him stronger?

574
00:30:46,376 --> 00:30:48,043
We'll see.

575
00:30:48,044 --> 00:30:51,881
Only a select few can become champions.

576
00:30:51,882 --> 00:30:53,147
Take this one.

577
00:30:55,135 --> 00:30:58,971
He loves tequila but rejects my blood.

578
00:30:58,972 --> 00:31:01,390
I call him General Houston.

579
00:31:01,391 --> 00:31:02,858
Fitting.

580
00:31:02,859 --> 00:31:04,292
Get the blood.

581
00:31:08,031 --> 00:31:09,947
See?

582
00:31:09,950 --> 00:31:13,951
No matter how you train
it or dress it up,

583
00:31:13,954 --> 00:31:15,404
it's a chicken.

584
00:31:15,405 --> 00:31:17,505
[bones crunching]

585
00:31:20,994 --> 00:31:24,929
And chickens lose their heads.

586
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:34,856
♪ ♪

587
00:31:37,223 --> 00:31:40,601
(man) They're coming in from the Alamo!

588
00:31:40,602 --> 00:31:42,502
(man) The survivors!

589
00:31:47,208 --> 00:31:49,742
- It's a baby.
- Hang on.

590
00:31:52,063 --> 00:31:53,329
(Smith) Whoa.

591
00:31:53,348 --> 00:31:54,515
Everyone just stand back.

592
00:31:54,516 --> 00:31:56,517
Get through.

593
00:31:56,518 --> 00:31:58,068
You, fetch Doc Ewing.

594
00:31:58,069 --> 00:31:59,403
We got a sickly woman here.

595
00:31:59,404 --> 00:32:00,687
- No, no, no, no, no!
- Don't worry.

596
00:32:00,688 --> 00:32:02,406
It's all right.
It's all right. Please.

597
00:32:02,407 --> 00:32:04,241
Hey, what do I do with this shit bugger?

598
00:32:04,242 --> 00:32:06,076
Give her to the doc?

599
00:32:06,077 --> 00:32:07,611
Make up a bedroom in my tent.

600
00:32:07,612 --> 00:32:09,079
We'll see come morning.

601
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:10,581
Now I'm a damn nursemaid.

602
00:32:10,582 --> 00:32:12,583
Everybody, stand back.
Get out of the way.

603
00:32:12,584 --> 00:32:14,118
(woman) Give me the baby.

604
00:32:14,119 --> 00:32:16,587
Let me help. Please, just let me help.

605
00:32:16,588 --> 00:32:18,255
[sobbing]

606
00:32:18,256 --> 00:32:19,590
(woman) It's gonna be all right.

607
00:32:19,591 --> 00:32:21,340
[baby crying]

608
00:32:21,342 --> 00:32:23,509
[sobbing]

609
00:32:23,511 --> 00:32:25,344
Ma'am?

610
00:32:25,346 --> 00:32:28,197
Ma'am, it's all right.

611
00:32:28,216 --> 00:32:29,766
It's all right, ma'am.

612
00:32:29,767 --> 00:32:32,769
Give me your hand.

613
00:32:32,770 --> 00:32:36,773
Please, ma'am,

614
00:32:36,774 --> 00:32:38,574
come with me.

615
00:32:40,562 --> 00:32:42,528
[cow mooing]

616
00:32:42,530 --> 00:32:50,636
♪ ♪

617
00:33:02,467 --> 00:33:03,683
Captain.

618
00:33:05,503 --> 00:33:07,671
Thank you.

619
00:33:07,672 --> 00:33:09,506
You all right?

620
00:33:09,507 --> 00:33:11,758
What happened?

621
00:33:11,759 --> 00:33:16,230
Where's Zachariah and Anderson?

622
00:33:16,231 --> 00:33:21,584
Anderson stayed back to bury Zacharias.

623
00:33:21,603 --> 00:33:23,202
Zachariah...

624
00:33:24,656 --> 00:33:26,289
You sure?

625
00:33:30,778 --> 00:33:32,595
Yeah.

626
00:33:42,207 --> 00:33:44,041
Had to be Comanches.

627
00:33:44,042 --> 00:33:45,758
I knew it was Comanches.

628
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,760
Fellows, were it Comanches?

629
00:33:47,762 --> 00:33:49,379
Nah, Karankawa.

630
00:33:49,380 --> 00:33:51,215
[shouting indistinctly]

631
00:33:51,216 --> 00:33:53,217
- Deaf, we going to Alamo?
- Mind your business!

632
00:33:53,218 --> 00:33:54,434
(man) Deaf, ain't you gonna go

633
00:33:54,435 --> 00:33:55,602
to the aid of our patriots?

634
00:33:55,603 --> 00:33:57,020
That's up to Sam Houston, son.

635
00:33:57,021 --> 00:33:59,022
- Who's she?
- Out of the way!

636
00:33:59,023 --> 00:34:02,726
(man) Deaf, what's going on, Deaf?

637
00:34:02,727 --> 00:34:04,561
- What about Travis?
- Crockett?

638
00:34:04,562 --> 00:34:07,296
Bowie?

639
00:34:07,315 --> 00:34:09,465
Dead.

640
00:34:09,484 --> 00:34:12,319
All dead, boys.

641
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:15,421
[all muttering]

642
00:34:19,744 --> 00:34:21,594
General.

643
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:26,750
(Smith) General Houston,

644
00:34:26,751 --> 00:34:29,303
this here's Emily West.

645
00:34:29,304 --> 00:34:31,821
Herself and Captain Dickinson's wife

646
00:34:31,839 --> 00:34:34,824
were among the few Alamo survivors.

647
00:34:34,842 --> 00:34:36,275
Ma'am.

648
00:34:37,562 --> 00:34:39,328
(Houston) Ms. West.

649
00:34:44,435 --> 00:34:45,584
Water.

650
00:35:12,714 --> 00:35:16,699
Santa Anna took no prisoners.

651
00:35:16,718 --> 00:35:21,504
We were spared to carry his message.

652
00:35:23,057 --> 00:35:25,559
He'll show no mercy...

653
00:35:25,560 --> 00:35:30,564
♪ ♪

654
00:35:30,565 --> 00:35:32,689
Killing all who oppose him.

655
00:35:32,690 --> 00:35:34,818
♪ ♪

656
00:35:34,819 --> 00:35:39,623
Plans to poison the wells and fields

657
00:35:39,624 --> 00:35:42,429
so that people never return.

658
00:35:44,245 --> 00:35:47,178
Burn every ranch, every settlement,

659
00:35:47,179 --> 00:35:48,661
every building.

660
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:52,832
♪ ♪

661
00:35:52,851 --> 00:35:57,321
Santa Anna has ordered General Urrea

662
00:35:57,322 --> 00:35:59,857
to attack Goliad for his next slaughter.

663
00:35:59,858 --> 00:36:01,859
(man) Mexicans attacking Goliad...

664
00:36:01,860 --> 00:36:06,747
♪ ♪

665
00:36:06,748 --> 00:36:09,200
He mocks you to his men.

666
00:36:09,201 --> 00:36:12,335
♪ ♪

667
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:14,121
He named a chicken after you.

668
00:36:14,122 --> 00:36:20,026
♪ ♪

669
00:36:20,045 --> 00:36:22,380
[sobbing]

670
00:36:22,381 --> 00:36:25,216
♪ ♪

671
00:36:25,217 --> 00:36:27,218
It's not wrong you survived.

672
00:36:27,219 --> 00:36:30,388
[sobbing]

673
00:36:30,389 --> 00:36:37,111
♪ ♪

674
00:36:37,112 --> 00:36:38,861
Chris, I just heard.

675
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:41,297
Santa Anna will show no mercy.

676
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,988
Tom, I got news.

677
00:36:46,989 --> 00:36:51,292
Santa Anna is moving 500
men on Goliad... 500 men.

678
00:36:51,293 --> 00:36:53,294
He's attacking Fannin at Goliad.

679
00:36:53,295 --> 00:36:56,213
I heard he named a damn
chicken after our general.

680
00:36:56,214 --> 00:36:58,215
(man) Goliad's next.

681
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:02,152
Slitherin' snake son of a
bitch means to wipe us out.

682
00:37:03,305 --> 00:37:05,105
(Wilkins) This is all messed up.

683
00:37:07,726 --> 00:37:09,844
Ma'am, we're gonna get
you to the medical tent

684
00:37:09,845 --> 00:37:11,945
and get some food in your belly.

685
00:37:15,033 --> 00:37:16,899
You should know they held out 12 days,

686
00:37:16,902 --> 00:37:18,751
waiting for you.

687
00:37:18,770 --> 00:37:20,753
Last thing I heard Colonel Travis yell

688
00:37:20,772 --> 00:37:22,872
was, "No surrender."

689
00:37:24,826 --> 00:37:27,278
Yeah, yeah.

690
00:37:27,279 --> 00:37:28,761
All right.

691
00:37:31,116 --> 00:37:32,432
(Houston) God damn it!

692
00:37:32,451 --> 00:37:34,368
Was I not appointed to
lead all Texian forces

693
00:37:34,369 --> 00:37:36,370
as commander in chief?

694
00:37:36,371 --> 00:37:38,172
- Was I?
- Yes, sir.

695
00:37:38,173 --> 00:37:41,274
Then why didn't they obey my
order to abandon the Alamo?

696
00:37:52,304 --> 00:37:54,204
I should have gone in myself.

697
00:37:56,308 --> 00:38:00,276
We can't let this sacrifice be in vain.

698
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:04,280
Their precious blood
bought us precious time.

699
00:38:04,282 --> 00:38:07,735
Let us not squander it.

700
00:38:07,736 --> 00:38:11,287
Deaf, as a loyal Texian citizen

701
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:12,873
and foremost authority on this land,

702
00:38:12,874 --> 00:38:16,877
I'd value your opinion about now.

703
00:38:16,878 --> 00:38:20,331
Deaf, do you understand me?

704
00:38:20,332 --> 00:38:23,016
I'm deaf, not dumb.

705
00:38:24,419 --> 00:38:26,152
San Antone is too close

706
00:38:26,171 --> 00:38:28,154
to Mexico proper to reinforce,

707
00:38:28,173 --> 00:38:31,974
too far from American
settlements to defend.

708
00:38:31,977 --> 00:38:36,097
We ought to move north of
Victoria, marshal our forces.

709
00:38:36,098 --> 00:38:40,333
Let Santa Anna get drunk on
an abundance of confidence.

710
00:38:40,352 --> 00:38:43,819
And then, General,

711
00:38:43,822 --> 00:38:46,256
we attack with a vengeance.

712
00:38:48,276 --> 00:38:50,611
♪ ♪

713
00:38:50,612 --> 00:38:53,614
If only I had 300 more rangers like you,

714
00:38:53,615 --> 00:38:55,950
I'd win this war in a day.

715
00:38:55,951 --> 00:38:58,085
I want you to ride to Goliad

716
00:38:58,086 --> 00:39:00,087
and, one more time, instruct Colonel Fannin

717
00:39:00,088 --> 00:39:02,206
to abandon his position there posthaste

718
00:39:02,207 --> 00:39:03,973
and rendezvous with us at Victoria.

719
00:39:07,762 --> 00:39:10,346
Make sure he understands
he'll be all by his lonesome

720
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:13,801
with enemy troops up his
ass within the week.

721
00:39:13,802 --> 00:39:17,820
Tell him this time, I said please.

722
00:39:19,224 --> 00:39:20,391
Yes, sir.

723
00:39:20,392 --> 00:39:23,359
I'll tell him.

724
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:25,712
Ready the men.

725
00:39:25,730 --> 00:39:28,331
Tomorrow at first light,
we march to Victoria.

726
00:39:32,787 --> 00:39:35,122
[indistinct conversations]

727
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:36,624
Prepare to retreat.

728
00:39:36,625 --> 00:39:38,159
Pass the word. We retreat.

729
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:39,875
Pass the word.

730
00:39:39,878 --> 00:39:41,328
(man) What the hell we waitin' for?

731
00:39:41,329 --> 00:39:44,430
[crowd murmuring]

732
00:40:00,498 --> 00:40:01,798
(both) Sarah.

733
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:03,416
(Burns) Mama taught me

734
00:40:03,417 --> 00:40:05,001
to ease a woman's burden
every chance I got.

735
00:40:05,002 --> 00:40:06,586
Yeah, well, she should've taught you

736
00:40:06,587 --> 00:40:08,136
not to be such a horse's ass.

737
00:40:08,138 --> 00:40:10,138
Oh, pardon my crass
friend's language, ma'am.

738
00:40:10,140 --> 00:40:12,140
Thank you, Truett. Thank you, Yancey.

739
00:40:12,142 --> 00:40:13,659
But unless you're injured,

740
00:40:13,677 --> 00:40:15,678
you're not allowed
inside the medical tent.

741
00:40:15,679 --> 00:40:19,015
Well, I got a serious cut
on my elbow someplace,

742
00:40:19,016 --> 00:40:21,184
and I'm pretty sure it
needs some liniment.

743
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:25,287
Yeah, well, I have a
badly bruised heart.

744
00:40:28,526 --> 00:40:31,009
Stop horsing around like
nothing happened today.

745
00:40:33,747 --> 00:40:37,584
We... we didn't want to scare you, Sarah.

746
00:40:37,585 --> 00:40:40,218
It's tragic sad about Zacharias.

747
00:40:43,707 --> 00:40:46,042
Don't fret about us.

748
00:40:46,043 --> 00:40:48,644
Truett here got his first scalp.

749
00:40:56,136 --> 00:40:58,687
Should've told her right away

750
00:40:58,689 --> 00:41:00,188
instead of trying to curry favor.

751
00:41:00,190 --> 00:41:01,858
It was your "bruised heart" manure

752
00:41:01,859 --> 00:41:03,041
that set her off.

753
00:41:03,060 --> 00:41:04,394
She was gonna treat my elbow.

754
00:41:04,395 --> 00:41:05,728
Treat your goddamn elbow...

755
00:41:05,729 --> 00:41:07,195
- She was.
- Ah, quit your bellyaching.

756
00:41:07,197 --> 00:41:08,731
- She would have.
- Quiet down, boys.

757
00:41:08,732 --> 00:41:10,617
- We got sick people here.
- Don't push me.

758
00:41:10,618 --> 00:41:12,584
You got me in trouble.

759
00:41:18,742 --> 00:41:20,410
(man) Don't you stand out on that ridge.

760
00:41:20,411 --> 00:41:22,795
They'll see you for a mile, son.

761
00:41:22,796 --> 00:41:24,797
Knowles.

762
00:41:24,798 --> 00:41:27,667
Hell you going, Private?

763
00:41:27,668 --> 00:41:29,768
Don't rightly know.

764
00:41:33,724 --> 00:41:34,841
You deserting?

765
00:41:34,842 --> 00:41:36,643
The army needs you, soldier.

766
00:41:36,644 --> 00:41:42,098
♪ ♪

767
00:41:42,099 --> 00:41:43,483
(man) It's all balls-up.

768
00:41:43,484 --> 00:41:44,817
Don't worry about it.

769
00:41:44,818 --> 00:41:51,824
♪ ♪

770
00:41:51,825 --> 00:41:53,425
[growling]

771
00:41:53,444 --> 00:41:54,676
Lookit there.

772
00:41:57,615 --> 00:41:58,831
(Elwood) That's a wolf.

773
00:41:58,832 --> 00:42:01,167
Mm, more like a wolf dog.

774
00:42:01,168 --> 00:42:03,602
Come here, boy.

775
00:42:03,621 --> 00:42:05,755
Come over here. Say howdy.

776
00:42:05,756 --> 00:42:07,457
You've been following us.

777
00:42:07,458 --> 00:42:09,008
- He ain't coming.
- Yep.

778
00:42:09,009 --> 00:42:11,010
Hey, that's my personal rabbit.

779
00:42:11,011 --> 00:42:12,978
It's requisitioned.

780
00:42:15,716 --> 00:42:16,933
[spits]

781
00:42:16,934 --> 00:42:18,635
- This a damn jackrabbit?
- Yeah.

782
00:42:18,636 --> 00:42:22,138
Smells like three-day-old possum.

783
00:42:22,139 --> 00:42:24,524
Pilfers a rabbit and complains.

784
00:42:24,525 --> 00:42:27,143
I seasoned that rabbit just right.

785
00:42:27,144 --> 00:42:29,529
Come on, boy. Look what I got for you.

786
00:42:29,530 --> 00:42:31,981
Lookie here. Come on.

787
00:42:31,982 --> 00:42:34,583
That mongrel's gonna
bite your arm clean off.

788
00:42:35,486 --> 00:42:36,736
Come on.

789
00:42:36,737 --> 00:42:38,488
Now I know why
they call you Beans...

790
00:42:38,489 --> 00:42:40,622
'cause that's the only
thing you can cook.

791
00:42:40,624 --> 00:42:41,790
Ha!

792
00:42:41,792 --> 00:42:43,459
[laughter]

793
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:44,976
He don't like your cookings, Beans.

794
00:42:44,995 --> 00:42:47,630
I saw that dog lick its own ass.

795
00:42:47,631 --> 00:42:48,814
He don't know.

796
00:42:48,832 --> 00:42:51,566
[laughter]

797
00:42:56,056 --> 00:42:57,724
(man) Ventured up, Captain...

798
00:42:57,725 --> 00:42:59,509
over on the right.

799
00:42:59,510 --> 00:43:01,060
(Burns) Captain?

800
00:43:01,061 --> 00:43:02,811
Uh, Captain?

801
00:43:02,813 --> 00:43:04,097
Captain?

802
00:43:04,098 --> 00:43:05,648
Young Truett here

803
00:43:05,649 --> 00:43:07,517
is grievously worried about his ma

804
00:43:07,518 --> 00:43:09,686
and requests a short leave of absence.

805
00:43:09,687 --> 00:43:12,689
Yeah, it's my mother
and my sisters, sir.

806
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:14,440
And, well, since I lost my daddy

807
00:43:14,441 --> 00:43:16,693
to typhoid three years ago, you know,

808
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:18,578
I'm the only man of the house.

809
00:43:18,579 --> 00:43:21,030
Yeah, and with that cutthroat
Santa Anna marching north,

810
00:43:21,031 --> 00:43:23,583
well, the Fincham family
ranch is right in his path.

811
00:43:23,584 --> 00:43:25,618
Yeah, I just want to make
sure they moved out.

812
00:43:25,619 --> 00:43:27,519
You know, shouldn't take
me more than a day or two

813
00:43:27,538 --> 00:43:29,789
just to get them someplace safe.

814
00:43:29,790 --> 00:43:31,791
And I request to go with him, Captain.

815
00:43:31,792 --> 00:43:33,960
Make sure he comes back.

816
00:43:33,961 --> 00:43:36,045
The boy can hardly wipe
himself without my counsel.

817
00:43:36,046 --> 00:43:37,630
Oh, shut up.

818
00:43:37,631 --> 00:43:39,610
He just want to run
into some more Indians

819
00:43:39,611 --> 00:43:41,700
so he can get a scalp like mine, sir.

820
00:43:45,723 --> 00:43:47,656
That all of it, then?

821
00:43:53,897 --> 00:43:55,114
One day.

822
00:43:55,115 --> 00:43:57,483
I'll give you all one day.

823
00:43:57,484 --> 00:44:01,154
Then you meet us in Goliad.

824
00:44:01,155 --> 00:44:02,405
- Get.
- Sir.

825
00:44:02,406 --> 00:44:03,656
Sir.

826
00:44:03,657 --> 00:44:04,957
If we leave in the morning,

827
00:44:04,958 --> 00:44:06,391
we can get there by noon.

828
00:44:08,495 --> 00:44:11,497
[fiddle playing gentle melody]

829
00:44:11,498 --> 00:44:16,586
♪ ♪

830
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:18,504
(man) Hunker down. It's ready.

831
00:44:18,505 --> 00:44:23,593
♪ ♪

832
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:25,478
(man) And that's looking good, fellows.

833
00:44:25,479 --> 00:44:27,146
Look at you.

834
00:44:27,147 --> 00:44:34,437
♪ ♪

835
00:44:34,438 --> 00:44:39,025
You a part of Stephen
Austin's rangering company?

836
00:44:39,026 --> 00:44:41,944
(Karnes) Glad you're back, Billy.

837
00:44:41,945 --> 00:44:43,613
Who's asking?

838
00:44:43,614 --> 00:44:46,115
Name's Beauregard.

839
00:44:46,116 --> 00:44:49,267
I hear tell you might
need an extra hand.

840
00:44:49,286 --> 00:44:51,970
Looks like you could use one too, Red.

841
00:44:57,928 --> 00:44:59,128
My mama'd throw that in the pot

842
00:44:59,129 --> 00:45:00,847
with the cayenne pepper
and call it gumbo.

843
00:45:00,848 --> 00:45:01,964
You from Louisiana?

844
00:45:01,965 --> 00:45:04,467
Crawled up from the bayou.

845
00:45:04,468 --> 00:45:08,187
Call me Gator... Gator Davis.

846
00:45:08,188 --> 00:45:10,473
Thought you was Beauregard.

847
00:45:10,474 --> 00:45:13,942
Gator Davis Beauregard,

848
00:45:13,944 --> 00:45:16,110
Esquire.

849
00:45:16,113 --> 00:45:18,496
I'm of a mind to join your outfit.

850
00:45:21,902 --> 00:45:25,321
You want to help Texas,
go join the army.

851
00:45:25,322 --> 00:45:26,989
Oh, no.

852
00:45:26,990 --> 00:45:29,641
My flat feet ain't suited for marching.

853
00:45:29,660 --> 00:45:32,126
I want to ranger around with y'all,

854
00:45:32,129 --> 00:45:34,145
help citizens directly.

855
00:45:42,172 --> 00:45:45,508
You got to furnish your
own horse and gun.

856
00:45:45,509 --> 00:45:47,009
Pays $1.25 a day,

857
00:45:47,010 --> 00:45:49,395
payable whenever Austin
raises the funds.

858
00:45:49,396 --> 00:45:53,099
Best see what he's made of first.

859
00:45:53,100 --> 00:45:54,666
Okeydokey by me.

860
00:45:57,321 --> 00:45:59,587
Introduce yourself to the fellers.

861
00:46:03,660 --> 00:46:05,593
That's all.

862
00:46:20,544 --> 00:46:23,645
[baby crying]

863
00:46:27,384 --> 00:46:29,567
Private, hold.

864
00:46:31,388 --> 00:46:33,538
I'm sorry to bother you, Mrs. Dickinson.

865
00:46:33,557 --> 00:46:35,224
Can you tell me,

866
00:46:35,225 --> 00:46:38,110
how many carriers did Santa Anna bring?

867
00:46:38,111 --> 00:46:41,113
How many soldiers?

868
00:46:41,114 --> 00:46:43,616
Kill them.

869
00:46:43,617 --> 00:46:45,033
Kill them all.

870
00:46:45,035 --> 00:46:53,091
♪ ♪

871
00:46:58,781 --> 00:47:00,581
(both) Sarah.

872
00:47:00,600 --> 00:47:02,901
General Houston wants
us to scout on ahead

873
00:47:02,902 --> 00:47:06,404
and track down Santa Anna.

874
00:47:06,405 --> 00:47:08,406
You've risked your lives enough.

875
00:47:08,407 --> 00:47:11,793
Why can't he send somebody
older, more experienced?

876
00:47:11,794 --> 00:47:15,630
I reckon 'cause...

877
00:47:15,631 --> 00:47:17,881
we's the best he got.

878
00:47:17,883 --> 00:47:21,586
Being heroes is our cross to bear.

879
00:47:21,587 --> 00:47:25,356
Now, my dear granny Lulu, she...

880
00:47:26,592 --> 00:47:28,143
She...

881
00:47:28,144 --> 00:47:31,346
She pressed this flower
in the family Bible

882
00:47:31,347 --> 00:47:33,230
on her wedding day.

883
00:47:33,232 --> 00:47:35,999
I want you to hold on to
that until I come back.

884
00:47:38,404 --> 00:47:40,522
- Thank you, Truett.
- Yeah.

885
00:47:40,523 --> 00:47:46,009
Uh, ma'am, you don't
have to give this back.

886
00:47:47,697 --> 00:47:51,499
It's a part of me that you are to keep

887
00:47:51,500 --> 00:47:54,584
long as the rivers run.

888
00:47:54,587 --> 00:47:55,704
"Long as the rivers run."

889
00:47:55,705 --> 00:47:56,871
Shut it.

890
00:47:56,872 --> 00:47:59,374
[giggles] Come here.

891
00:47:59,375 --> 00:48:07,481
♪ ♪

892
00:48:08,801 --> 00:48:10,302
I'll be madder than a wet hen

893
00:48:10,303 --> 00:48:12,403
if anything happens to either of you.

894
00:48:14,774 --> 00:48:17,791
So doggone it, you better
take care of each other.

895
00:48:19,945 --> 00:48:21,696
Yes, ma'am.

896
00:48:21,697 --> 00:48:22,697
Yes, ma'am.

897
00:48:22,698 --> 00:48:28,653
♪ ♪

898
00:48:28,654 --> 00:48:31,573
- Ooh, she likes me.
- She hugged me tighter.

899
00:48:31,574 --> 00:48:32,574
- Did not.
- Did too.

900
00:48:32,575 --> 00:48:34,743
- Did not.
- Did so.

901
00:48:34,744 --> 00:48:36,260
Boy...

902
00:48:38,581 --> 00:48:40,582
(Flores) [speaking Spanish]

903
00:48:40,583 --> 00:48:43,684
_

904
00:48:44,906 --> 00:48:47,702
_

905
00:48:48,875 --> 00:48:50,279
_

906
00:48:52,320 --> 00:48:53,321
_

907
00:48:53,725 --> 00:48:55,122
_

908
00:48:57,400 --> 00:48:58,665
For who?

909
00:49:00,403 --> 00:49:02,404
You can ride with the rangers,

910
00:49:02,405 --> 00:49:05,322
kill Mexicans for them.

911
00:49:05,324 --> 00:49:08,325
But if you think you'll
ever be one of them,

912
00:49:08,327 --> 00:49:09,527
you're a fool.

913
00:49:09,528 --> 00:49:12,947
Fighting for the revolution.

914
00:49:12,948 --> 00:49:16,500
We're losing, Manuel,

915
00:49:16,502 --> 00:49:17,834
and I don't trust the Anglos

916
00:49:17,837 --> 00:49:20,205
any more than the Santanistas.

917
00:49:20,206 --> 00:49:21,355
What becomes of us?

918
00:49:21,374 --> 00:49:22,856
We'll be free.

919
00:49:22,875 --> 00:49:26,544
Santa Anna promises the
same if we fight for him.

920
00:49:26,545 --> 00:49:31,633
Who do you trust more,
for your family's sake,

921
00:49:31,634 --> 00:49:33,400
Santa Anna or Houston?

922
00:49:55,908 --> 00:49:57,292
- Working on it.
- Yep.

923
00:49:57,293 --> 00:49:58,743
If you stop saying...

924
00:49:58,744 --> 00:50:00,995
[cow mooing]

925
00:50:00,996 --> 00:50:02,664
(Wilkins) Reckon it ain't my cooking

926
00:50:02,665 --> 00:50:05,667
the dog don't like,

927
00:50:05,668 --> 00:50:07,651
Henry.

928
00:50:11,390 --> 00:50:14,491
[coughing]

929
00:50:18,431 --> 00:50:19,981
Got a pint in my saddlebag.

930
00:50:19,982 --> 00:50:21,599
You need a slug to ease the pain?

931
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:24,185
I'm fine,

932
00:50:24,186 --> 00:50:25,569
but before we go to Goliad,

933
00:50:25,571 --> 00:50:27,254
I got to take the buckboard back...

934
00:50:27,273 --> 00:50:30,442
pay respects to the missus.

935
00:50:30,443 --> 00:50:32,292
See you at sunup.

936
00:50:35,614 --> 00:50:39,451
♪ ♪

937
00:50:39,452 --> 00:50:42,436
[sobbing softly]

938
00:50:42,455 --> 00:50:47,625
♪ ♪

939
00:50:47,626 --> 00:50:49,627
(man) Pack those up front.

940
00:50:49,628 --> 00:50:51,379
You should be going first.

941
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:56,885
♪ ♪

942
00:50:56,886 --> 00:50:58,553
(Gator) Seems like your tune

943
00:50:58,554 --> 00:51:00,454
is distressing the youngster, señor.

944
00:51:00,473 --> 00:51:02,956
Let me see that guitar.

945
00:51:02,975 --> 00:51:05,894
You gonna take that from
a greenhorn, Flores?

946
00:51:05,895 --> 00:51:08,829
I'm gonna lighten the mood
for you, little lady.

947
00:51:09,899 --> 00:51:12,734
[playing<i> Turkey in the Straw]</i>

948
00:51:12,735 --> 00:51:15,537
[cheerful vibrant melody]

949
00:51:15,538 --> 00:51:19,640
♪ ♪

950
00:51:19,658 --> 00:51:21,326
Well, now all we needs is a jug

951
00:51:21,327 --> 00:51:23,460
and a sweet little gal to poke.

952
00:51:23,462 --> 00:51:31,568
♪ ♪

953
00:51:39,979 --> 00:51:41,813
[upbeat guitar duet playing]

954
00:51:41,814 --> 00:51:43,647
(man) She wants you, Deaf.

955
00:51:43,649 --> 00:51:51,705
♪ ♪

956
00:52:10,509 --> 00:52:11,876
What do you think, Captain?

957
00:52:11,877 --> 00:52:13,761
It's growing on me.

958
00:52:13,762 --> 00:52:21,868
♪ ♪

959
00:52:29,361 --> 00:52:33,531
[coyote howls]

960
00:52:33,532 --> 00:52:36,534
- I got to go.
- Go away from here.

961
00:52:36,535 --> 00:52:39,537
You stink like a she
goat at mating time.

962
00:52:39,538 --> 00:52:41,155
[laughter]

963
00:52:41,156 --> 00:52:44,541
We don't want to smell
your shit all night.

964
00:52:44,543 --> 00:52:45,709
[grunts]

965
00:52:45,711 --> 00:52:46,711
[man shouts in Spanish]

966
00:52:46,712 --> 00:52:48,878
[gunshot]

967
00:52:48,881 --> 00:52:51,982
[grunting]

968
00:52:52,918 --> 00:52:55,920
[grunts and gargles]

969
00:52:55,921 --> 00:52:58,021
[gagging]

970
00:53:00,593 --> 00:53:03,595
[haunting music]

971
00:53:03,596 --> 00:53:11,702
♪ ♪

972
00:53:24,633 --> 00:53:31,771
♪ ♪

973
00:53:31,773 --> 00:53:33,105
[crowd shouting]

974
00:53:33,108 --> 00:53:35,392
(man) Hey, hey, hey! Hey,<i> vamos!</i>

975
00:53:35,393 --> 00:53:37,443
[shouting in Spanish]

976
00:53:37,445 --> 00:53:38,946
[cheers and applause]

977
00:53:38,947 --> 00:53:40,698
(man) Hey, hey, hey!

978
00:53:40,699 --> 00:53:43,800
[cheers and applause]

979
00:53:57,799 --> 00:53:59,899
8 pesos, Presidente.

980
00:54:01,169 --> 00:54:04,270
[cheering quiets]

981
00:54:08,059 --> 00:54:10,895
I did not bet that bird,<i> chuparlo.</i>

982
00:54:10,896 --> 00:54:12,945
Yes, you did,<i> mi General.</i>

983
00:54:14,849 --> 00:54:16,734
8 pesos.

984
00:54:16,735 --> 00:54:19,904
How is it you have 8 pesos to bet with?

985
00:54:19,905 --> 00:54:22,288
As a fact, I do, Excellency.

986
00:54:25,994 --> 00:54:28,094
You have not been paid.

987
00:54:30,248 --> 00:54:32,515
If you have 8 pesos...

988
00:54:36,254 --> 00:54:39,790
You robbed them from the women refugees.

989
00:54:39,791 --> 00:54:42,376
And if you robbed them,
you raped them also.

990
00:54:42,377 --> 00:54:43,877
No, no, no,<i> mi General.</i>

991
00:54:43,878 --> 00:54:45,528
I know this.

992
00:54:48,049 --> 00:54:50,968
Do you know what "magnanimous" is?

993
00:54:50,969 --> 00:54:52,219
No, sir.

994
00:54:52,220 --> 00:54:55,889
Then, though you did not win,

995
00:54:55,890 --> 00:55:01,979
raped grandmothers, and
lied to your<i> General,</i>

996
00:55:01,980 --> 00:55:03,314
I pay you.

997
00:55:03,315 --> 00:55:07,985
I pay you because we are victorious

998
00:55:07,986 --> 00:55:11,087
and to show you what "magnanimous" is.

999
00:55:17,245 --> 00:55:20,346
[cheers and applause]

1000
00:55:28,056 --> 00:55:30,823
Do not try such a trick again.

1001
00:55:35,897 --> 00:55:38,766
Enough rest and celebration.

1002
00:55:38,767 --> 00:55:40,985
Almonte, assume command.

1003
00:55:40,986 --> 00:55:42,418
Yes, General.

1004
00:55:44,439 --> 00:55:46,843
_

1005
00:55:49,198 --> 00:55:51,046
_

1006
00:55:51,962 --> 00:55:54,336
_

1007
00:55:54,866 --> 00:55:56,200
_

1008
00:55:56,201 --> 00:56:00,337
[birds chirping]

1009
00:56:00,338 --> 00:56:03,040
[insects buzzing]

1010
00:56:03,041 --> 00:56:05,257
[cheerful bluegrass music playing]

1011
00:56:05,260 --> 00:56:06,943
[rhythmic clapping]

1012
00:56:06,961 --> 00:56:09,946
[cheering and whistling]

1013
00:56:09,964 --> 00:56:14,051
♪ ♪

1014
00:56:14,052 --> 00:56:16,053
<i>Buenas noches,</i> Juan.

1015
00:56:16,054 --> 00:56:20,974
♪ ♪

1016
00:56:20,975 --> 00:56:22,860
As you were.

1017
00:56:22,861 --> 00:56:30,967
♪ ♪

1018
00:56:39,411 --> 00:56:41,412
(Houston) Emily?

1019
00:56:41,413 --> 00:56:43,396
It's Sam.

1020
00:56:46,919 --> 00:56:49,136
I brought you some fresh
clothes and something to eat...

1021
00:56:49,137 --> 00:56:50,820
You're as blustery as ever, Sam.

1022
00:56:50,839 --> 00:56:52,139
And you are...

1023
00:56:52,140 --> 00:56:54,141
I'm alive.

1024
00:56:54,142 --> 00:56:57,109
A long way from the French Quarter.

1025
00:56:59,848 --> 00:57:02,114
You still have that scarf I gave you.

1026
00:57:04,486 --> 00:57:06,953
Don't own much of nothing else.

1027
00:57:08,490 --> 00:57:10,173
Emily, I don't flatter myself

1028
00:57:10,191 --> 00:57:12,175
that you came all this way to see me.

1029
00:57:12,193 --> 00:57:13,944
I came seeking my brother, Jupiter,

1030
00:57:13,945 --> 00:57:16,947
to purchase his freedom.

1031
00:57:16,948 --> 00:57:20,117
Texas is slave free.

1032
00:57:20,118 --> 00:57:22,134
If'n you say so.

1033
00:57:23,755 --> 00:57:27,124
I located him at the Alamo Mission,

1034
00:57:27,125 --> 00:57:28,876
and I told him he was free,

1035
00:57:28,877 --> 00:57:32,713
but he stayed to fight,

1036
00:57:32,714 --> 00:57:37,050
ended up one of the last survivors,

1037
00:57:37,051 --> 00:57:41,487
and I watched as Santa
Anna had him executed.

1038
00:57:44,192 --> 00:57:47,710
Jupiter liked to fight.

1039
00:57:47,729 --> 00:57:49,128
A family trait.

1040
00:57:52,033 --> 00:57:54,300
At least he died a free man.

1041
00:57:57,455 --> 00:57:59,456
I want you to spend a
few days recuperating,

1042
00:57:59,457 --> 00:58:01,074
and then I'm gonna get you safe passage

1043
00:58:01,075 --> 00:58:02,159
back to New Orleans.

1044
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:03,410
No.

1045
00:58:03,411 --> 00:58:09,383
I'm of a mind to stay in Texas,

1046
00:58:09,384 --> 00:58:11,017
join the cause.

1047
00:58:13,922 --> 00:58:17,641
I could use a horse.

1048
00:58:17,642 --> 00:58:21,193
Well, let's discuss that
in the morning, shall we?

1049
00:58:24,015 --> 00:58:26,249
It's good to rest my eyes on you again.

1050
00:58:26,267 --> 00:58:27,867
Sam...

1051
00:58:30,104 --> 00:58:33,539
Jupiter was all I had in this world.

1052
00:58:36,995 --> 00:58:40,697
At least he died a hero.

1053
00:58:40,698 --> 00:58:43,466
He was more a Texian than any of us.

1054
00:58:46,371 --> 00:58:48,020
Get some rest.

1055
00:58:58,266 --> 00:59:01,367
[birds chirping]

1056
00:59:13,815 --> 00:59:16,450
♪ ♪

1057
00:59:16,451 --> 00:59:19,453
You are and always will
be my sweet desert rose.

1058
00:59:19,454 --> 00:59:20,821
Deaf!

1059
00:59:20,822 --> 00:59:23,323
♪ ♪

1060
00:59:23,324 --> 00:59:26,976
Come, come.

1061
00:59:31,716 --> 00:59:33,166
Close your eyes.

1062
00:59:33,167 --> 00:59:34,334
All right.

1063
00:59:34,335 --> 00:59:36,152
All right. Don't move.

1064
00:59:42,427 --> 00:59:44,276
(Elena) Papa Deaf...

1065
00:59:48,349 --> 00:59:51,852
This poor little soul lost her mama.

1066
00:59:51,853 --> 00:59:55,171
Far as I know, there's no
way to look after her.

1067
00:59:55,189 --> 00:59:57,991
What's her name?

1068
00:59:57,992 --> 01:00:01,627
Elena, just like your own ma.

1069
01:00:05,867 --> 01:00:08,300
And this mangy orphan here...

1070
01:00:10,255 --> 01:00:13,757
[clicks tongue]

1071
01:00:13,758 --> 01:00:15,042
[dog whimpers]

1072
01:00:15,043 --> 01:00:16,892
Call him Half Breed.

1073
01:00:18,046 --> 01:00:19,129
[sighs]

1074
01:00:19,130 --> 01:00:21,131
[stream rushing]

1075
01:00:21,132 --> 01:00:24,233
[buffalo lowing]

1076
01:00:40,151 --> 01:00:42,051
About how much further to San Antone?

1077
01:00:42,070 --> 01:00:44,003
Three or four days at least.

1078
01:00:50,244 --> 01:00:54,046
[bluegrass music playing]

1079
01:00:54,048 --> 01:00:55,716
(Hays) How do, ma'am?

1080
01:00:55,717 --> 01:00:58,401
I'll have a glass of that whiskey, please.

1081
01:00:58,419 --> 01:01:00,403
(Luther) Well...

1082
01:01:00,421 --> 01:01:02,055
Looks like we got ourselves a greenhorn

1083
01:01:02,056 --> 01:01:03,757
come across the river.

1084
01:01:03,758 --> 01:01:05,926
(man) Settle down, Luther. Leave him be.

1085
01:01:05,927 --> 01:01:07,260
Yeah, you.

1086
01:01:07,261 --> 01:01:09,895
I'm talking about you.

1087
01:01:09,897 --> 01:01:13,032
(Luther) I can smell you like a fat sow.

1088
01:01:14,686 --> 01:01:17,787
[indistinct conversations]

1089
01:01:23,244 --> 01:01:25,878
Lila, get.

1090
01:01:32,370 --> 01:01:34,037
You remind me of everything

1091
01:01:34,038 --> 01:01:36,673
I come out West to get away from.

1092
01:01:36,674 --> 01:01:37,923
(Hays) Then I reckon

1093
01:01:37,925 --> 01:01:40,776
your quarrel is with your past,

1094
01:01:40,795 --> 01:01:42,111
not me.

1095
01:01:42,130 --> 01:01:45,231
[laughter]

1096
01:01:50,855 --> 01:01:51,954
[glass clatters]

1097
01:01:51,973 --> 01:01:53,857
[music stops]

1098
01:01:53,858 --> 01:01:55,241
[laughs]

1099
01:01:58,780 --> 01:02:01,898
Now, that was ill-mannered.

1100
01:02:01,899 --> 01:02:04,201
You'll need to replace my drink

1101
01:02:04,202 --> 01:02:06,203
or face consequences.

1102
01:02:06,204 --> 01:02:08,822
[laughs]

1103
01:02:08,823 --> 01:02:11,124
[laughter]

1104
01:02:11,125 --> 01:02:14,293
This some sort of halfwit idiot,

1105
01:02:14,295 --> 01:02:15,962
or is he just plain stupid?

1106
01:02:15,963 --> 01:02:18,715
(man) You're drunk, Luther.

1107
01:02:18,716 --> 01:02:20,717
Neither.

1108
01:02:20,718 --> 01:02:22,085
Must just be you.

1109
01:02:22,086 --> 01:02:23,170
[hisses]

1110
01:02:23,171 --> 01:02:24,820
Go on.

1111
01:02:26,474 --> 01:02:28,392
Don't let nothing but fear stop you.

1112
01:02:28,393 --> 01:02:30,394
(man) Leave it be!

1113
01:02:30,395 --> 01:02:31,395
[growls]

1114
01:02:31,396 --> 01:02:33,013
[gunshot]

1115
01:02:33,014 --> 01:02:35,015
(Wallace) Ah, settle down, boys.

1116
01:02:35,016 --> 01:02:37,283
Don't you even try it.

1117
01:02:39,070 --> 01:02:42,739
[groaning]

1118
01:02:42,740 --> 01:02:45,075
That was a fair fight,
and we all saw it.

1119
01:02:45,076 --> 01:02:48,078
A polite gesture, sir, but I can manage.

1120
01:02:48,079 --> 01:02:51,364
Now, can someone please go fetch

1121
01:02:51,365 --> 01:02:55,919
whomsoever it is around here
that administers justice?

1122
01:02:55,920 --> 01:02:57,887
We need to report this.

1123
01:03:01,375 --> 01:03:04,810
Well, ain't you all gussied up?

1124
01:03:05,930 --> 01:03:07,846
Lupe's big on the pampering.

1125
01:03:07,849 --> 01:03:09,466
Oh.

1126
01:03:09,467 --> 01:03:11,268
You got clean clothes,

1127
01:03:11,269 --> 01:03:15,972
and you got a new young
'UN and a wolf-dog pet.

1128
01:03:15,973 --> 01:03:17,856
Well, Lupe must be as happy

1129
01:03:17,859 --> 01:03:20,292
as a bumblebee in a flower patch.

1130
01:03:21,979 --> 01:03:25,232
Yeah, may as well hang up my spurs,

1131
01:03:25,233 --> 01:03:28,235
move to town, work at the general feed.

1132
01:03:28,236 --> 01:03:30,287
(Karnes) [laughs]

1133
01:03:30,288 --> 01:03:34,706
Well, you are getting
awful old, my friend.

1134
01:03:34,709 --> 01:03:37,376
Henry, it's 20 miles to go yet.

1135
01:03:37,378 --> 01:03:40,379
Try to keep up.

1136
01:03:40,381 --> 01:03:42,348
Yah!

1137
01:03:51,541 --> 01:03:53,808
Thing?

1138
01:03:57,931 --> 01:04:02,685
I hear tell you're gonna go
fight for Texas, Hard Case.

1139
01:04:02,686 --> 01:04:05,387
Mister, you making light of me?

1140
01:04:05,388 --> 01:04:07,389
Well, after seeing you handle a gun,

1141
01:04:07,390 --> 01:04:10,392
that'd be a pretty dumb idea.

1142
01:04:10,393 --> 01:04:11,727
Name's William Wallace.

1143
01:04:11,728 --> 01:04:13,778
Folks call me Bigfoot.

1144
01:04:13,780 --> 01:04:15,397
On account of you're big?

1145
01:04:15,398 --> 01:04:17,700
That, but mostly 'cause I once

1146
01:04:17,701 --> 01:04:20,536
killed a Cherokee with big feet.

1147
01:04:20,537 --> 01:04:24,323
Bigfoot Wallace, John Coffee Hays.

1148
01:04:24,324 --> 01:04:25,973
Named after Colonel John Coffee,

1149
01:04:25,992 --> 01:04:29,662
protégé of President Andrew Jackson.

1150
01:04:29,663 --> 01:04:30,829
Call me Jack.

1151
01:04:30,830 --> 01:04:32,313
Jack.

1152
01:04:33,833 --> 01:04:35,834
Are... are you some kind of

1153
01:04:35,835 --> 01:04:38,319
genuine blue blood or something?

1154
01:04:40,890 --> 01:04:42,758
Something.

1155
01:04:42,759 --> 01:04:45,827
[laughing]

1156
01:04:45,845 --> 01:04:47,995
You see, I'm on my way
to the Alamo Mission

1157
01:04:48,014 --> 01:04:51,850
in San Antonio, to Bexar, to enlist.

1158
01:04:51,851 --> 01:04:54,669
Well, I'm afraid you're a mite late, son.

1159
01:04:56,489 --> 01:04:58,339
Colonel Travis was
killed by the Mexicans,

1160
01:04:58,358 --> 01:05:02,361
along with everybody else at the Alamo.

1161
01:05:02,362 --> 01:05:03,795
Crockett?

1162
01:05:08,201 --> 01:05:10,536
He was gonna be U.S. president someday.

1163
01:05:10,537 --> 01:05:12,520
Yes, sir.

1164
01:05:12,539 --> 01:05:14,472
They got the whole damn lot of them.

1165
01:05:17,510 --> 01:05:19,510
I'm on my way to fight
alongside my brother

1166
01:05:19,512 --> 01:05:22,196
at Fort Defiance in Goliad.

1167
01:05:22,215 --> 01:05:23,981
Colonel Fannin's command?

1168
01:05:25,852 --> 01:05:27,952
Reckon then I'll enlist there.

1169
01:05:31,725 --> 01:05:34,542
Better ride with me, then, Hard Case.

1170
01:05:34,561 --> 01:05:37,896
I don't need you waylaid
in any more gunfights.

1171
01:05:37,897 --> 01:05:40,899
[cheerful music]

1172
01:05:40,900 --> 01:05:49,658
♪ ♪

1173
01:05:49,659 --> 01:05:51,542
You coming or what?

1174
01:05:51,544 --> 01:05:59,650
♪ ♪

1175
01:06:05,258 --> 01:06:08,359
[militaristic drumming]

1176
01:06:13,817 --> 01:06:15,616
(man) Come on, now.

1177
01:06:27,947 --> 01:06:30,715
We bring you orders
from General Houston.

1178
01:06:38,708 --> 01:06:40,709
No doubt ordering me to withdraw.

1179
01:06:40,710 --> 01:06:42,544
I know we're in a general retreat.

1180
01:06:42,545 --> 01:06:45,446
But the Mexican army is weeks away.

1181
01:06:45,465 --> 01:06:47,448
Colonel, if you don't get,

1182
01:06:47,467 --> 01:06:50,401
you and your men are gonna
be overrun and die.

1183
01:06:53,473 --> 01:06:55,974
I'll do what my conscience
tells me to do, boy.

1184
01:06:55,975 --> 01:06:58,360
God damn your conscience.

1185
01:06:58,361 --> 01:06:59,862
Do what Houston tells you.

1186
01:06:59,863 --> 01:07:02,231
You follow orders.

1187
01:07:02,232 --> 01:07:03,649
We're with you, Colonel.

1188
01:07:03,650 --> 01:07:05,651
Dismissed.

1189
01:07:05,652 --> 01:07:07,403
Dismissed, gentlemen.

1190
01:07:07,404 --> 01:07:09,738
[scoffs]

1191
01:07:09,739 --> 01:07:12,006
We delivered the message.

1192
01:07:14,911 --> 01:07:16,727
Houston...

1193
01:07:20,366 --> 01:07:23,218
(Fincham) Our good wagon and
our old mare ain't here.

1194
01:07:23,219 --> 01:07:26,255
Ma and the girls... they
must've left already.

1195
01:07:26,256 --> 01:07:29,591
(Burns) So who's that
stallion belong to, then?

1196
01:07:29,592 --> 01:07:31,576
[grunting]

1197
01:07:44,240 --> 01:07:45,840
(Fincham) Yah. Come on.

1198
01:07:57,787 --> 01:07:59,887
[gasping]

1199
01:08:04,711 --> 01:08:08,297
Private Knowles? What the hell?

1200
01:08:08,298 --> 01:08:10,632
Last we heard, youse was desertin'.

1201
01:08:10,633 --> 01:08:11,866
Now you profiteering?

1202
01:08:11,885 --> 01:08:13,200
Well, hold up, now.

1203
01:08:13,219 --> 01:08:15,352
I done my duty, is what I done.

1204
01:08:15,355 --> 01:08:16,704
Alls I did is,

1205
01:08:16,723 --> 01:08:19,391
I warned the old lady
about the Mexicans.

1206
01:08:19,392 --> 01:08:20,893
Can't help it if she's running off

1207
01:08:20,894 --> 01:08:23,527
all scared and leaving shit.

1208
01:08:23,530 --> 01:08:25,564
That old lady is my mother,

1209
01:08:25,565 --> 01:08:26,732
you despicable poltroon.

1210
01:08:26,733 --> 01:08:28,617
You... you loot my home?

1211
01:08:28,618 --> 01:08:30,885
Your mother?

1212
01:08:30,904 --> 01:08:32,821
He done bamboozled your family, Truett.

1213
01:08:32,822 --> 01:08:34,957
What are you gonna do about it?

1214
01:08:34,958 --> 01:08:37,808
Now, just... easy, gentlemen.

1215
01:08:38,828 --> 01:08:42,546
Well, it seems you forgot

1216
01:08:42,549 --> 01:08:45,215
my daddy's prized bullwhip, Knowles.

1217
01:08:45,218 --> 01:08:46,969
So I'ma give it to you.

1218
01:08:46,970 --> 01:08:48,235
Now, now, hold on... ahh!

1219
01:08:48,254 --> 01:08:50,339
You damn deserter, get!

1220
01:08:50,340 --> 01:08:53,441
[Knowles wailing, whip cracking]

1221
01:08:57,647 --> 01:08:58,814
[gunshot]

1222
01:08:58,815 --> 01:08:59,997
- Oh, what the hell?
- Yee-haw!

1223
01:08:59,999 --> 01:09:01,817
[horse whinnies]

1224
01:09:01,818 --> 01:09:05,903
You hoodwink anybody
else, we tie you down...

1225
01:09:05,905 --> 01:09:06,904
Gentlemen...

1226
01:09:06,906 --> 01:09:08,607
We pour molasses on you.

1227
01:09:08,608 --> 01:09:11,527
We let the critters eat their fill.

1228
01:09:11,528 --> 01:09:13,829
Now get on your horse and get.

1229
01:09:13,830 --> 01:09:15,364
[whip cracks]

1230
01:09:15,365 --> 01:09:17,098
I'm going. I'm going.

1231
01:09:26,709 --> 01:09:28,759
I showed him.

1232
01:09:28,761 --> 01:09:32,014
Gol'darn thieving
deserter, you better get!

1233
01:09:32,015 --> 01:09:33,882
[bugle playing]

1234
01:09:33,883 --> 01:09:36,885
[indistinct chatter]

1235
01:09:36,886 --> 01:09:39,888
[bugle continues]

1236
01:09:39,889 --> 01:09:47,995
♪ ♪

1237
01:09:51,034 --> 01:09:54,468
That's good enough. Climb
out and cover them up.

1238
01:09:54,487 --> 01:09:56,822
Not sure I agree with
your methods, General.

1239
01:09:56,823 --> 01:09:59,456
Worked for Washington and Jackson.

1240
01:09:59,459 --> 01:10:03,511
All right, men, stand
beside me bearing arms.

1241
01:10:14,307 --> 01:10:17,808
I promised you men an answer.

1242
01:10:17,810 --> 01:10:19,910
I'm now prepared to deliver it.

1243
01:10:23,349 --> 01:10:27,903
I've ordered Colonel Fannin
to retreat from Goliad.

1244
01:10:27,904 --> 01:10:31,607
Our armies will move east
and join forces with his,

1245
01:10:31,608 --> 01:10:34,491
picking up volunteers along the way.

1246
01:10:34,494 --> 01:10:38,280
This is the very kind of deliberation

1247
01:10:38,281 --> 01:10:42,784
that lost the lives of our
compatriots at the Alamo!

1248
01:10:42,785 --> 01:10:46,788
Sir, we lost great men in Travis

1249
01:10:46,789 --> 01:10:51,259
and Davy Crockett and Jim Bowie himself.

1250
01:10:51,260 --> 01:10:53,010
General,

1251
01:10:53,012 --> 01:10:55,362
I feel it is our Christian duty

1252
01:10:55,381 --> 01:10:57,865
to march to Goliad to fight.

1253
01:10:57,884 --> 01:11:00,802
To defeat Santa Anna, to take

1254
01:11:00,803 --> 01:11:04,940
our vengeance, and stand our ground

1255
01:11:04,941 --> 01:11:07,476
with Fannin is the proper,

1256
01:11:07,477 --> 01:11:11,813
tactically, thing to do, sir.

1257
01:11:11,814 --> 01:11:12,981
(man) He's right!

1258
01:11:12,982 --> 01:11:14,698
We should fight!

1259
01:11:14,701 --> 01:11:16,867
(all) Yeah!

1260
01:11:16,869 --> 01:11:18,836
Men...

1261
01:11:26,579 --> 01:11:28,378
(Houston) Colonel Fannin has his orders.

1262
01:11:28,381 --> 01:11:30,564
You men have yours.

1263
01:11:30,583 --> 01:11:34,885
You may question my military strategy

1264
01:11:34,887 --> 01:11:37,839
but not my heart,

1265
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:41,391
and if any one of you
question my command,

1266
01:11:41,394 --> 01:11:43,944
there's a grave reserved for you.

1267
01:11:49,435 --> 01:11:50,936
I will give you your battle.

1268
01:11:50,937 --> 01:11:53,754
I will give you your blood.

1269
01:11:53,773 --> 01:11:56,525
Your brothers and friends
shall be avenged,

1270
01:11:56,526 --> 01:11:59,576
and it will be when and where
your general orders it.

1271
01:11:59,579 --> 01:12:01,530
Now let me hear you say aye.

1272
01:12:01,531 --> 01:12:03,597
(all) Aye.

1273
01:12:03,616 --> 01:12:05,834
I'm not asking a question.

1274
01:12:05,835 --> 01:12:08,837
Answer so that God and
Santa Anna can hear it.

1275
01:12:08,838 --> 01:12:10,872
Let me hear you say aye!

1276
01:12:10,873 --> 01:12:12,541
(all) Aye!

1277
01:12:12,542 --> 01:12:15,643
[all shouting]

1278
01:12:21,968 --> 01:12:23,600
Good.

1279
01:12:23,603 --> 01:12:25,387
You are dismissed.

1280
01:12:25,388 --> 01:12:26,821
General.

1281
01:12:32,645 --> 01:12:33,979
(Houston) Captain Baker,

1282
01:12:33,980 --> 01:12:36,398
tearing off on some half-assed reprisal

1283
01:12:36,399 --> 01:12:38,734
is exactly what Santa Anna wants.

1284
01:12:38,735 --> 01:12:41,451
You insubordinate me again
in front of my troops,

1285
01:12:41,454 --> 01:12:43,453
I'll have you shot.

1286
01:12:43,456 --> 01:12:49,510
♪ ♪

1287
01:12:52,213 --> 01:12:53,513
- Come on! Come on!
- Come on!

1288
01:12:53,515 --> 01:12:54,847
[both shouting]

1289
01:12:54,849 --> 01:12:56,182
Spurs are not that hard!

1290
01:12:56,184 --> 01:12:57,867
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- I beat you, boy.

1291
01:12:57,886 --> 01:12:59,535
- You didn't beat me.
- I beat you.

1292
01:12:59,554 --> 01:13:02,038
You couldn't beat a blind dog, boy.

1293
01:13:02,057 --> 01:13:03,607
[laughter]

1294
01:13:03,608 --> 01:13:06,110
Third time this week.

1295
01:13:06,111 --> 01:13:07,526
Yee, boy, I done beat you!

1296
01:13:07,529 --> 01:13:08,861
No, I beat you.

1297
01:13:08,863 --> 01:13:10,713
I'm faster than a ring-tailed bobcat.

1298
01:13:10,732 --> 01:13:12,399
- You seen me.
- Hell you are.

1299
01:13:12,400 --> 01:13:14,401
I was a full nose ahead,
ain't that right, Captain?

1300
01:13:14,402 --> 01:13:16,052
- Where you off to?
- Back to camp.

1301
01:13:16,071 --> 01:13:17,955
Fannin's a stubborn bastard.
Won't obey orders.

1302
01:13:17,956 --> 01:13:22,126
Well, you want us to
linger and spy on him?

1303
01:13:22,127 --> 01:13:24,495
What do you reckon, Deaf?

1304
01:13:24,496 --> 01:13:26,497
They're wearin' their own boots.

1305
01:13:26,498 --> 01:13:28,165
Can walk where they want to.

1306
01:13:28,166 --> 01:13:30,549
If Fannin hasn't moved
by day after next,

1307
01:13:30,552 --> 01:13:33,052
ride due east and meet
us there, in Victoria.

1308
01:13:33,054 --> 01:13:35,738
[coughing]

1309
01:13:35,757 --> 01:13:39,593
And keep your eyes and ears open.

1310
01:13:39,594 --> 01:13:40,761
And don't you tarry.

1311
01:13:40,762 --> 01:13:42,479
You feeling poorly, Captain?

1312
01:13:42,480 --> 01:13:43,913
I'm fine, damn it.

1313
01:13:43,932 --> 01:13:47,583
Well, we... we just wanted
to say that, well,

1314
01:13:47,602 --> 01:13:49,486
we feel that it's the...

1315
01:13:49,487 --> 01:13:51,655
What my jibber-jabbering
friend means to say

1316
01:13:51,656 --> 01:13:54,090
is that we hold the two of
you in equal high regard

1317
01:13:54,109 --> 01:13:55,541
as our own daddies.

1318
01:13:58,613 --> 01:14:01,097
And we proud to be Texan rangers, sirs.

1319
01:14:02,617 --> 01:14:05,551
You two may become real rangers yet.

1320
01:14:10,842 --> 01:14:13,844
- Real rangers.
- Oh, yeah.

1321
01:14:13,845 --> 01:14:19,850
♪ ♪

1322
01:14:19,851 --> 01:14:21,051
[horse whinnies]

1323
01:14:21,052 --> 01:14:23,053
- Help! Help us!
- Ahh, help!

1324
01:14:23,054 --> 01:14:28,607
[people shouting]

1325
01:14:28,610 --> 01:14:30,793
Help! My ankle!

1326
01:14:30,812 --> 01:14:32,128
(man) I can't get it off her.

1327
01:14:32,147 --> 01:14:34,732
(man) Keep her head above the water.

1328
01:14:34,733 --> 01:14:36,066
Come to the back! Help lift!

1329
01:14:36,067 --> 01:14:37,151
(man) Flores, get in there.

1330
01:14:37,152 --> 01:14:38,819
Get in there.

1331
01:14:38,820 --> 01:14:41,655
(Elwood) She's stuck.
Don't lift till I say.

1332
01:14:41,656 --> 01:14:44,708
One, two... lift! Agh!

1333
01:14:44,709 --> 01:14:49,213
[water splashing]

1334
01:14:49,214 --> 01:14:51,597
(man) Take a look at her.

1335
01:14:53,802 --> 01:14:56,903
[sobbing and coughing]

1336
01:15:02,093 --> 01:15:04,076
- Thank you.
- You all right, darling?

1337
01:15:05,597 --> 01:15:06,597
Shit.

1338
01:15:06,598 --> 01:15:08,098
Name's Rebecca Pitt.

1339
01:15:08,099 --> 01:15:10,082
That's my brother, Colby.

1340
01:15:11,486 --> 01:15:12,853
All right.

1341
01:15:12,854 --> 01:15:16,023
Awful pretty name... Rebecca.

1342
01:15:16,024 --> 01:15:17,908
Name's Kit Acklin.

1343
01:15:17,909 --> 01:15:20,543
Me and Vern there are ridin'
with the rangering company.

1344
01:15:23,164 --> 01:15:26,132
Well, good luck, Rebecca.

1345
01:15:27,702 --> 01:15:30,303
All right. Let's go, boy. Come on.

1346
01:15:37,879 --> 01:15:39,096
(woman) No, no, no.

1347
01:15:39,097 --> 01:15:40,563
Y'all done made a hustle out...

1348
01:15:40,582 --> 01:15:41,680
But you said two, not three.

1349
01:15:41,683 --> 01:15:42,683
- What is this?
- [grunts]

1350
01:15:42,684 --> 01:15:44,533
Huh? Whoa.

1351
01:15:44,552 --> 01:15:46,436
Now, you... do you
understand what this is?

1352
01:15:46,437 --> 01:15:47,721
Now, I told you...

1353
01:15:47,722 --> 01:15:49,723
What's that commotion over there?

1354
01:15:49,724 --> 01:15:52,442
Looks like that bastard's
demanding compensation

1355
01:15:52,443 --> 01:15:54,728
from the widow woman for
helping her to ford the river.

1356
01:15:54,729 --> 01:15:57,046
- Just gonna give you two...
- Hey, easy, easy, now.

1357
01:15:57,065 --> 01:16:00,067
That's the private that deserted
Gonzalez three days ago.

